        <updateDate>2023-11-08T21:02:08Z</updateDate>
        <cdata>
          <text>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Student Mental Health Rights Act&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This bill addresses mental health and substance use at institutions of higher education (IHEs).&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Specifically, the bill requires the Department of Education (ED)&amp;nbsp;to solicit information from students and conduct a study on mental health disabilities and substance use disorders at IHEs.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;In addition, ED must&amp;nbsp;issue guidance on&amp;nbsp;IHEs' (1) compliance&amp;nbsp;with&amp;nbsp;federal law on mental health, (2) legal obligations to&amp;nbsp;students with mental health disabilities and students with substance use disorders, and (3) policies that may have a discriminatory impact on such students.&lt;/p&gt;</text>
        </cdata>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
